abstract.value: The Tamiment Library and Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives Printed Ephemera Collection of Government Publications contains pamphlets and publications from federal governments around the world, publications from United States governmental departments, as well as from US state and municipal governments. The collection ranges in date from 1894-1988. Generally, the countries represented were/are related to communism. For instance there are pamphlets from Cuba, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, the Democratic Republic of Vietnam, the German Democratic Republic, and the Soviet Union. The US national, state, and municipal files relate primarily to economics, foreign affairs, labor, social security, and unemployment.

Materials in this collection have been compiled by the Tamiment Library. There is no accession record associated with this collection.

Series IV: Municipal Government Publications, 1903-1962, consists of files mainly from New York City, including a list of registered voters from 1912. Departments and agencies represented include: the Department of Labor, the Bureau of Standards, and the Works Progress Administration (WPA). In the WPA files are reports, a supervisor's and foreman's handbook, and reprints of talks given to WPA executives as part of the Executive Training Program. In addition to New York City, this series consists of files from Chicago and Detroit both containing Mayoral reports on race relations.
